subsection.def:
Commissioner
                    (關長) means the Commissioner of Customs and
                Excise and any Deputy or Assistant Commissioner of Customs and Excise;

licence
                    (特許) means a licence granted under
                    section 5;

place
                    (地方) means any area on land or water and
                includes any building, structure or enclosure, whether moveable or not;

register
                    (登記冊) means the register kept by the
                Commissioner under section 31;

paragraph.content:
to require the production of any book or document relating to the business
                    concerned, including any licence or other document relating to a person’s right
                    to manufacture optical discs;

to inspect, remove and detain for the purpose of examination for so long as
                    the Commissioner may consider necessary and to examine and copy any such
                    licence, book or document;

to remove and detain for the purpose of examination for so long as the
                    Commissioner may consider necessary and to examine samples of optical discs
                    found in the licensed premises;
